question: "but I certainly consider rude if you go in someone's shop to try and steal clients for your own shop". Who is the shop owner of bisq2? "incentivizing sellers to burn bsq to get reputation". Who is making money on it? And why is someone "stealing" a customer if the shop denies for him to sell in his shop because of a to low reputation. The guy wanting to sell would simply ask the person who wants to buy in the shop but finds no seller, to go outside of the shop, so one can sell to him there. Because the shop doesn't allow for one to sell in the shop because one is having a to low of a reputation.

question: i have not used bisq2 for a while. When i run it asked if i would like to update to bis2.1.8. I downloaded the files and ran the new version.
